field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Reshma2B: RuO2 sputtered at 200C, Powd1A: RuO2 powder dropcast from THF, powdIr1A:IrO2 powder dropcast from THF
field_data.Removed from vacuum: in air since test in O18 two days ago

notes: 18H29_Reshma2B_O18/01... ~ zero isotope exchange (link 1) Looks identical to 18H27/RuO2_200C_18O/01... but shifted by 30(!) mV Activity resembles exactly that on RHE scale of Reshma2A_O18 on the latter's way down (17 mV shift on RE scale) Shit! Current starts running away at cycle 32. There must be a shunt. Can't use anything after that (O2 at 5300s and 5500s should have been the same). Powd1A: 01... tonnes of CO2 on first cycles. Resistor changed to 100 Ohm after cycle 39 (0.757 vs RE, 1.47 vs RHE), is repeated at 500 Ohm and then at 100 Ohm. Makes a factor about 5/3 difference in current (30 uA to 50 uA). Clear degradation of OER current after that. Ramping up, repeating 0.717 vs RE (1.43 vs RHE) every now and then to see if it's actual degradation and not just something that only lasts a pulse. Looks in mass-time like there's something at m/z=72, but can't see it in mass spectra... hm... more active for OER after doing a bit of HER (link 2) CO doesn't poison HER very much. CO stripping attempt doesn't give significantly more CO2 than background, but the long pause at 0V vs RHE helped OER (3500 s in 17:34:42) Reducing it has made it much much much more active! link 1: https://cinfdata.fysik.dtu.dk/sniffer/xyplot.php?type=masstime&xmin=1700&xmax=2300&matplotlib=checked&title=&xlabel=&left_ylabel=&right_ylabel=&left_ymin=0.95e-12&left_ymax=2.05e-12&right_ymin=0&right_ymax=2.5e-10&left_plotlist%5B%5D=12579&right_plotlist%5B%5D=12578&chosen_group%5B%5D=2018-08-29+11%3A32%3A31 link 2: https://cinfdata.fysik.dtu.dk/sniffer/xyplot.php?type=masstime&xmin=0&xmax=3000&matplotlib=checked&title=&xlabel=&left_ylabel=&right_ylabel=&left_logscale=checked&left_ymin=0&left_ymax=0&right_ymin=0&right_ymax=0&left_plotlist%5B%5D=12667&left_plotlist%5B%5D=12668&left_plotlist%5B%5D=12669&left_plotlist%5B%5D=12670&left_plotlist%5B%5D=12671&left_plotlist%5B%5D=12672&left_plotlist%5B%5D=12673&chosen_group%5B%5D=2018-08-29+17%3A34%3A42 IrO2: crocodile clip of working was initially contacting the electrolyte -- currents all higher than 0
